<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-59-0566 </DOCNO><TEXT>A nozzle tip for a burner on a pulverized fuel-fired furnace for receivinga stream of pulverized fuel and air discharging from the burner and directingsaid pulverized fuel and air stream into the furnace, said nozzle tiphaving a hollow, open-ended end cap of particularly temperature resistantmaterial replaceably mounted to the base body; and a replaceable hollow,open-ended insert of particularly highly abrasion resistant materialpositioned within the end cap to form a concentric nozzle body havinga first flow passage through the hollow interior of the insert for passinga stream of pulverized fuel and air into the furnace and a second flowpassage through the annular space between the concentrically disposedinsert and end cap for passing a stream of additional air into the furnace.3 figs.</TEXT></DOC>